-- Daimler’s Bernhard Given 5-Year Contract, Handelsblatt Says
-- B y   A l e x   W e b b
-- 2012-02-07T18:01:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-07/daimler-s-bernhard-given-5-year-contract-handelsblatt-says.html
Daimler AG  board member Wolfgang Bernhard, who is deputy head of the Mercedes brand, has been
given a new five-year contract, Handelsblatt reported in a
preview of an article to be published tomorrow, citing
unidentified people with knowledge of the contract.  The appointment puts Bernhard in prime position to succeed
Dieter Zetsche as Daimler’s chief executive officer,
Handelsblatt said.  Marc Binder, a spokesman for Daimler, didn’t immediately
respond to an e-mail and telephone call seeking comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Webb in Frankfurt at 
 awebb25@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
